summary: NEW POKÉMON TCG CARDS & MERCH FOR DETECTIVE PIKACHU MOVIE REVEALED
title: NEW POKÉMON TCG CARDS & MERCH FOR DETECTIVE PIKACHU MOVIE REVEALED
body:
Today from the floor of the American International Toy Fair in New York, The Pokémon Company International revealed three new cards for the Pokémon Trading Card (TCG) game featuring Mr. Mime, JigglyPuff and Psyduck, as seen in the upcoming live-action movie, “POKÉMON Detective Pikachu.” These Pokémon were some of the breakout stars from the highly-viewed first trailer for the movie.

Like the Detective Pikachu,Charizard, and Greninja TCG cards previously announced, the newly revealed cards depict the Pokémon in their CGI movie likenesses and will be available at retail starting April 2 in the U.S.

For a first look at these cards and more from the “POKÉMON Detective Pikachu” merchandise line from Pokémon and PokemonCenter.com, visit The Pokémon Company International at Booth #3049 at The American International Toy Fair through Tuesday, February 19.
